A HIGH frequency network run by First Glasgow has been shortlisted in the bus industry Oscars. City bus service up for award A HIGH frequency network run by First Glasgow has been shortlisted in the bus industry Oscars.The awards recognise and reward the people, projects and organisations which positively deliver for their customers.The Glasgow operation's simpliCITY, which aims to have buses every 10 minutes or better, has been shortlisted in the Making Buses a Better Choice category of the UK Bus Awards to be announced in next month.First Glasgow managing director Fiona Kerr said: &quot;We believe we have delivered one of the UK's best bus networks and see more people using our buses with an increase in customer satisfaction.&quot; 